\title{Latchbio Integration}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Latch platform for bioinformatics workflows. Build pipelines with Latch SDK, @workflow/@task decorators, deploy serverless workflows, LatchFile/LatchDir, Nextflow/Snakemake integration."}

\subtree{
\title{LatchBio Integration}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Latch is a Python framework for building and deploying bioinformatics workflows as serverless pipelines. Built on Flyte, create workflows with @workflow/@task decorators, manage cloud data with LatchFile/LatchDir, configure resources, and integrate Nextflow/Snakemake pipelines.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\p{The Latch platform provides four main areas of functionality:}

\subtree{
\title{1. Workflow Creation and Deployment}
\ul{
\li{Define serverless workflows using Python decorators}
\li{Support for native Python, Nextflow, and Snakemake pipelines}
\li{Automatic containerization with Docker}
\li{Auto-generated no-code user interfaces}
\li{Version control and reproducibility}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Data Management}
\ul{
\li{Cloud storage abstractions (LatchFile, LatchDir)}
\li{Structured data organization with Registry (Projects → Tables → Records)}
\li{Type-safe data operations with links and enums}
\li{Automatic file transfer between local and cloud}
\li{Glob pattern matching for file selection}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Resource Configuration}
\ul{
\li{Pre-configured task decorators (@small_task, @large_task, @small_gpu_task, @large_gpu_task)}
\li{Custom resource specifications (CPU, memory, GPU, storage)}
\li{GPU support (K80, V100, A100)}
\li{Timeout and storage configuration}
\li{Cost optimization strategies}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Verified Workflows}
\ul{
\li{Production-ready pre-built pipelines}
\li{Bulk RNA-seq, DESeq2, pathway analysis}
\li{AlphaFold and ColabFold for protein structure prediction}
\li{Single-cell tools (ArchR, scVelo, emptyDropsR)}
\li{CRISPR analysis, phylogenetics, and more}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Start}
\subtree{
\title{Installation and Setup}
\pre{\startverb
# Install Latch SDK
python3 -m uv pip install latch

# Login to Latch
latch login

# Initialize a new workflow
latch init my-workflow

# Register workflow to platform
latch register my-workflow
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Prerequisites:}}

\ul{
\li{Docker installed and running}
\li{Latch account credentials}
\li{Python 3.8+}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Basic Workflow Example}
\pre{\startverb
from latch import workflow, small_task
from latch.types import LatchFile

@small_task
def process_file(input_file: LatchFile) -> LatchFile:
    """Process a single file"""
    # Processing logic
    return output_file

@workflow
def my_workflow(input_file: LatchFile) -> LatchFile:
    """
    My bioinformatics workflow

    Args:
        input_file: Input data file
    """
    return process_file(input_file=input_file)
\stopverb}
}
}

